1
00:00:18,685 --> 00:00:20,519
( hisses )

2
00:00:23,757 --> 00:00:26,291
<i>( eerie music playing )</i>

3
00:00:38,671 --> 00:00:40,672
<i>( insects chirping )</i>

4
00:00:42,575 --> 00:00:45,244
Man: <i>I BELIEVE</i>
<i>THAT THERE ARE DIFFERENT</i>
<i>LEVELS OF EVIL IN THE WORLD.</i>

5
00:00:50,817 --> 00:00:53,185
<i>NO RITUALS, NO MAGIC.</i>

6
00:00:53,187 --> 00:00:55,587
<i>IT ALREADY DWELLS</i>
<i>IN ALL OF US-- THAT'S IT,</i>

7
00:00:55,589 --> 00:00:56,789
<i>THAT'S THE BATTLE.</i>

8
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:05,764
<i>THIS IS WAR.</i>

9
00:01:05,766 --> 00:01:08,067
<i>THERE'S NO NEUTRAL GROUND.</i>

10
00:01:18,144 --> 00:01:21,080
- ( playing harmonica tune )
- ( girls laugh )

11
00:01:21,082 --> 00:01:22,714
Man:
<i>NEVER NEVER COME UP...</i>

12
00:01:23,716 --> 00:01:25,250
COME ON.

13
00:01:25,252 --> 00:01:27,286
( chattering )

14
00:01:48,374 --> 00:01:50,642
- AH!
- ASSHOLE.

15
00:01:56,116 --> 00:01:59,218
NO.  OW!
EASY, BUDDY.

16
00:02:01,554 --> 00:02:03,789
WOULD YOU RELAX?
COME ON.

17
00:02:06,626 --> 00:02:09,261
I DON'T LIKE
BEING OUT HERE.
IT CREEPS ME OUT.

18
00:02:10,230 --> 00:02:11,897
NO ONE ASKED YOU
TO COME.

19
00:02:11,899 --> 00:02:15,400
- WE'RE TRESPASSING.
- DO YOU HEAR THIS SHIT, BABY?

20
00:02:15,402 --> 00:02:17,402
WHAT ARE YOU
AFRAID OF ANYWAYS?

21
00:02:17,404 --> 00:02:21,140
JANET HOBBS
CAME OUT HERE
FIVE YEARS AGO,

22
00:02:21,142 --> 00:02:23,442
WENT MISSING,
NEVER CAME BACK.

23
00:02:23,444 --> 00:02:25,344
YEAH WELL, JANET HOBBS
WAS A NUTJOB.

24
00:02:25,346 --> 00:02:28,280
- SHE WASN'T THE ONLY ONE.
- I DON'T SEE WHAT THE BIG
DEAL IS ANYWAYS.

25
00:02:28,282 --> 00:02:30,616
- IT'S JUST AN OLD HOUSE.
- I THINK YOU'RE JUST SCARED.

26
00:02:30,618 --> 00:02:32,818
AND I THINK
YOU'RE GONNA BE FINISHING
ALL BY YOURSELF TONIGHT.

27
00:02:32,820 --> 00:02:34,820
YOU SERIOUS?

28
00:02:34,822 --> 00:02:36,922
THE GRANVILLE PLACE
IS HAUNTED.

29
00:02:36,924 --> 00:02:39,925
- WHAT ARE YOU GUYS
TALKING ABOUT?
- MARTHA MAY?

30
00:02:39,927 --> 00:02:42,794
CRAZY CHICK FROM THE '80s,
POSSESSED BY A DEMON.

31
00:02:42,796 --> 00:02:44,897
( screaming )

32
00:02:44,899 --> 00:02:47,399
( demonic voice )
S-U-E-D-O-M-S-A.

33
00:02:47,401 --> 00:02:49,701
-  <i>( wind blowing )</i>
<i>- IT DID ALL KINDS</i>
<i>OF FREAKY SHIT TO HER.</i>

34
00:02:49,703 --> 00:02:51,637
- <i>( thunder crashes )</i>
<i>- ( screaming )</i>

35
00:02:55,308 --> 00:02:57,376
YOU ARE
SO FULL OF SHIT.

36
00:02:57,378 --> 00:02:59,311
MY MOM
WENT TO HIGH SCHOOL
WITH THAT LADY.

37
00:03:00,780 --> 00:03:02,948
SHE HAD AN AFFAIR
WITH THIS GUY
FROM ACROSS TOWN.

38
00:03:04,684 --> 00:03:05,817
( exhales )

39
00:03:05,819 --> 00:03:08,187
SHE COULDN'T
HANDLE THE GUILT.

40
00:03:08,189 --> 00:03:09,922
( creaks )

41
00:03:10,890 --> 00:03:12,291
IT DROVE HER CRAZY.

42
00:03:14,194 --> 00:03:15,327
( shaky breath )

43
00:03:15,329 --> 00:03:17,396
I HEARD SHE COMMITTED
SUICIDE OUT THERE.

44
00:03:17,398 --> 00:03:20,666
- THAT'S A LIE.
- OKAY, THEN WHAT
REALLY HAPPENED, WISE-ASS?

45
00:03:20,668 --> 00:03:22,334
THE REAL QUESTION IS

46
00:03:22,336 --> 00:03:24,937
WHAT'S THE TOWN
HIDING FROM US?

47
00:03:26,739 --> 00:03:29,408
- <i>( coyote howls )</i>
<i>-</i> <i>( wind gusting )</i>

48
00:03:31,477 --> 00:03:33,345
I WANNA SEE IT.

49
00:03:33,347 --> 00:03:35,414
Woman:
NO!  FORGET ABOUT IT!

50
00:03:35,416 --> 00:03:37,549
ARE YOU
OUT OF YOUR MIND?

51
00:03:37,551 --> 00:03:38,984
I WANNA SEE
WHAT'S OUT THERE.

52
00:03:38,986 --> 00:03:41,353
( moans )
SUSIE, NO.

53
00:03:41,355 --> 00:03:43,822
WE'VE GROWN UP WITH THESE
STORIES OUR WHOLE LIFE.

54
00:03:43,824 --> 00:03:45,657
AREN'T YOU CURIOUS
WHAT'S OUT THERE?

55
00:03:45,659 --> 00:03:47,392
THAT'S JUST IT,
IT'S JUST STORIES.

56
00:03:47,394 --> 00:03:50,229
- THERE'S NOTHING OUT THERE.
- IT'S LIKE--

57
00:03:50,231 --> 00:03:53,799
IT'S LIKE
A BAD PLACE, MAN.

58
00:03:53,801 --> 00:03:55,267
<i>IT'S LIKE...</i>

59
00:03:56,002 --> 00:03:57,736
VERY BAD.

60
00:04:05,478 --> 00:04:08,247
- Woman #2: <i>SUSIE!</i>
<i>- SHE'LL BE DEAD BY MORNING.</i>

61
00:04:08,249 --> 00:04:09,281
( chuckles )

62
00:04:17,023 --> 00:04:19,825
<i>- ( footsteps )</i>
<i>- ( owl hooting )</i>

63
00:04:51,891 --> 00:04:53,292
( kisses )

64
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:07,973
( creaking )

65
00:05:10,843 --> 00:05:12,344
HELLO?

66
00:05:17,550 --> 00:05:19,751
Susie:
THIS PLACE IS
FREAKIN' CREEPY.

67
00:05:23,589 --> 00:05:25,390
WHAT THE HELL
IS THIS SHIT?

68
00:05:26,959 --> 00:05:29,061
( scoffs )
ARE YOU JOKING?
I MEAN THIS IS

69
00:05:29,063 --> 00:05:31,396
FREAKIN' WEIRD.

70
00:05:33,066 --> 00:05:35,067
- WHO THE HELL WOULD
EVEN LIVE HERE?
- HEY HEY.

71
00:05:35,069 --> 00:05:36,735
- I MEAN--
- HEY HEY HEY!

72
00:05:36,737 --> 00:05:38,537
WE'RE FINALLY
ALONE NOW.

73
00:05:38,539 --> 00:05:40,706
YOU PROMISED.

74
00:05:45,678 --> 00:05:47,012
<i>( bangs )</i>

75
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:50,582
THAT'S TOO ROUGH FOR ME.

76
00:05:50,584 --> 00:05:51,983
IT'S TOO ROUGH
FOR ME.

77
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:57,422
SOMETHING DOESN'T
FEEL RIGHT.

78
00:06:00,927 --> 00:06:02,127
NATHAN?

79
00:06:02,129 --> 00:06:03,862
<i>NATHAN!</i>

80
00:06:03,864 --> 00:06:06,098
- <i>NATHAN?!</i>
<i>- ( moans )</i>

81
00:06:13,373 --> 00:06:14,539
( gasps )

82
00:06:15,842 --> 00:06:17,142
NATHAN?

83
00:06:18,144 --> 00:06:19,578
NATHAN.

84
00:07:11,564 --> 00:07:13,165
<i>( birds chirp )</i>

85
00:07:26,746 --> 00:07:28,613
<i>( engine stops )</i>

86
00:07:30,684 --> 00:07:34,186
- SHERIFF HENDRICKS, RIGHT?
- YEAH, WE SPOKE ON THE PHONE.

87
00:07:34,188 --> 00:07:36,154
I'M MICHAEL BRODIE,
THIS IS MY WIFE RACHEL.

88
00:07:36,156 --> 00:07:38,490
- NICE TO MEET YOU.
- HI.  YOU TOO.

89
00:07:38,492 --> 00:07:42,093
- HAVE ANY TROUBLE FINDING US?
- YOUR TOWN DOESN'T REALLY
APPEAR ON MOST MAPS.

90
00:07:42,095 --> 00:07:44,162
IT'S ALWAYS HARD TO SEE
WHAT'S RIGHT IN FRONT
OF YOUR FACE.

91
00:07:45,798 --> 00:07:47,232
( laughs )
I'M--

92
00:07:47,234 --> 00:07:50,235
I'M JUST MESSIN' WITH YOU.
NOT EVEN ON MOST MAPS.

93
00:07:50,237 --> 00:07:52,204
LISTEN, I-- UH, I--
I REALLY APPRECIATE

94
00:07:52,206 --> 00:07:53,972
WHAT YOU'RE DOING HERE.

95
00:07:53,974 --> 00:07:55,807
OH YEAH, GLAD TO HELP,
GLAD TO HELP.

96
00:07:55,809 --> 00:07:58,477
IT'S NOT EVERY DAY WE GET
A BIG-CITY DETECTIVE HERE.

97
00:07:59,545 --> 00:08:01,480
THE TRUTH IS MY DEPUTY
BAILED TOWN LAST MINUTE,

98
00:08:01,482 --> 00:08:03,014
SO I WAS BOUND TO HIRE
THE FIRST PERSON
THAT CALLED.

99
00:08:03,016 --> 00:08:06,852
( laughs )
MOST FOLKS WHO COME HERE

100
00:08:06,854 --> 00:08:08,753
ARE USUALLY RUNNING
FROM SOMETHING.

101
00:08:08,755 --> 00:08:11,490
THAT OR THEY GOT
NO PLACE ELSE TO GO.

102
00:08:11,492 --> 00:08:13,992
I'M NOT RUNNING FROM ANYTHING.
WE'RE JUST LOOKING
FOR SOMETHING NEW.

103
00:08:13,994 --> 00:08:16,828
AIN'T WE ALL?
AIN'T WE ALL?

104
00:08:16,830 --> 00:08:19,664
ANYWAY, WINTER MONTHS ARE
USUALLY PRETTY QUIET HERE.

105
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:21,266
POPULATION JUST
UNDER A THOUSAND.

106
00:08:21,268 --> 00:08:24,035
<i>WE'RE JUST SIMPLE FOLK</i>
<i>REALLY, JUST--</i>

107
00:08:24,037 --> 00:08:25,737
IT'S THE WAY
I LIKE TO KEEP IT.

108
00:08:25,739 --> 00:08:27,706
ALL RIGHT.

109
00:08:33,946 --> 00:08:36,281
IT'S REALLY AMAZING.

110
00:08:36,283 --> 00:08:38,550
<i>( birds chirping )</i>

111
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:44,155
UGH.  ALL RIGHT,
THIS IS THE PLACE.

112
00:08:44,157 --> 00:08:46,157
THERE YOU GO.

113
00:08:46,159 --> 00:08:47,692
THANK YOU.

114
00:08:47,694 --> 00:08:50,729
- YOU'RE WELCOME.
- OH, IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

115
00:08:50,731 --> 00:08:53,198
YEAH, THIS IS ONE
OF OUR SUMMER RENTALS.

116
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:55,600
UH, THE FAMILY DOESN'T
COME UP TILL JUNE

117
00:08:55,602 --> 00:08:58,103
SO YOU GUYS ARE WELCOME
TO USE IT UNTIL YOU
FIND A PLACE.

118
00:08:58,105 --> 00:09:00,205
OKAY, THANK YOU.

119
00:09:00,207 --> 00:09:02,941
UNIFORM, GUN, BADGE.

120
00:09:02,943 --> 00:09:05,176
ALL RIGHT, I GUESS
I'LL LEAVE YOU GUYS ALONE.

121
00:09:05,178 --> 00:09:06,978
- LET YOU GET SETTLED IN.
- THANK YOU.

122
00:09:06,980 --> 00:09:08,847
- THANKS.
- YOU'RE WELCOME, WELCOME.

123
00:09:08,849 --> 00:09:10,782
UM, I'LL PICK YOU UP
IN THE MORNING?

124
00:09:10,784 --> 00:09:12,918
- YEAH.
- WELCOME TO GLENWOOD BAY.

125
00:09:17,056 --> 00:09:21,226
( breathes deeply )
WELL, HERE WE GO.

126
00:09:21,228 --> 00:09:23,128
HERE WE GO.

127
00:10:18,351 --> 00:10:20,652
( waves lapping )

128
00:10:44,143 --> 00:10:46,711
- I MADE US BREAKFAST.
- YEAH.

129
00:10:48,714 --> 00:10:50,749
<i>( phone ringing )</i>

130
00:10:54,286 --> 00:10:56,087
THIS IS MIKE.

131
00:10:56,089 --> 00:10:57,288
<i>UH-HUH.</i>

132
00:11:00,326 --> 00:11:02,193
WHAT DO YOU NORMALLY DO?

133
00:11:03,429 --> 00:11:05,397
REALLY?
( snorts )

134
00:11:05,399 --> 00:11:08,033
NO, OKAY,
I'LL BE THERE.

135
00:11:08,035 --> 00:11:10,035
I'LL LEAVE RIGHT NOW.

136
00:11:10,037 --> 00:11:11,770
( sighs )

137
00:11:11,772 --> 00:11:13,872
WHAT WAS
THAT ABOUT?

138
00:11:13,874 --> 00:11:15,440
IT WAS HENDRICKS.

139
00:11:15,442 --> 00:11:18,043
FIRST DAY ON THE JOB,
ALREADY A MISSING PERSON.

140
00:11:19,145 --> 00:11:22,047
I THOUGHT MAYBE WE COULD
HAVE BREAKFAST TOGETHER.

141
00:11:22,049 --> 00:11:24,416
I'M SORRY, RACH, YOU KNOW
THERE'S A MISSING PERSON.

142
00:11:24,418 --> 00:11:26,751
I'M ALREADY LATE.

143
00:11:28,788 --> 00:11:30,188
MMMM.

144
00:11:38,898 --> 00:11:40,732
HAVE A GOOD DAY.

145
00:12:09,729 --> 00:12:12,163
( rushing water )

146
00:12:19,739 --> 00:12:22,040
( heavy breathing )

147
00:12:26,479 --> 00:12:28,780
<i>( birds chirping )</i>

148
00:12:34,987 --> 00:12:37,455
<i>( footsteps )</i>

149
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:50,435
( heavy breathing )

150
00:12:50,437 --> 00:12:52,270
( sniffles )

151
00:12:54,507 --> 00:12:56,441
<i>( child laughing )</i>

152
00:13:04,784 --> 00:13:06,785
Rachel: <i>HELLO?</i>

153
00:13:08,788 --> 00:13:09,954
<i>HELLO.</i>

154
00:13:11,423 --> 00:13:13,158
ARE YOU OKAY?

155
00:13:19,298 --> 00:13:21,065
MY HUSBAND AND I

156
00:13:21,067 --> 00:13:23,201
LIVE IN THE HOUSE
OVER THERE.

157
00:13:25,070 --> 00:13:27,071
I SHOULDN'T BE HERE.

158
00:13:27,073 --> 00:13:28,339
MY SISTER LEFT ME HERE.

159
00:13:29,308 --> 00:13:30,842
I HAVE TO GO.

160
00:13:31,811 --> 00:13:33,478
WAIT UP.

161
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:34,913
HOLD UP.
LET ME JUST--

162
00:13:36,849 --> 00:13:38,483
- ...HELP YOU.
-  <i>( wind gusts )</i>

163
00:13:38,485 --> 00:13:40,285
<i>( glass breaks )</i>

164
00:13:47,827 --> 00:13:49,861
<i>( birds chirping )</i>

165
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:57,268
Mike:
SO WHO'S
THE MISSING PERSON?

166
00:13:57,270 --> 00:13:59,304
Sheriff:
SOME LOCAL TEEN GIRL.

167
00:13:59,306 --> 00:14:02,540
IT'S WEIRD.
IT'S NOT EVERY DAY WE GET
TO DO REAL POLICE WORK.

168
00:14:04,443 --> 00:14:07,278
- YEAH, WHAT'S THAT?
- THAT?

169
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:09,480
THE LILY AMONG THORNS.

170
00:14:09,482 --> 00:14:12,550
IT'S A SHIELD TO THOSE
WHO WALK IN INTEGRITY,

171
00:14:12,552 --> 00:14:14,619
GUARDING THE PATHS
OF JUSTICE AND...

172
00:14:14,621 --> 00:14:16,521
...AND WATCHING OVER
THE WAY OF HIS SAINTS.

173
00:14:16,523 --> 00:14:19,157
IT'S PROVERBS 2,
VERSE SEVEN AND EIGHT.

174
00:14:21,961 --> 00:14:23,628
YOU A RELIGIOUS MAN?

175
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:26,164
GOD-FEARING.
YOU?

176
00:14:26,166 --> 00:14:28,566
( scoffs ) NO.

177
00:14:28,568 --> 00:14:30,435
NOT ANYMORE.

178
00:14:31,971 --> 00:14:33,571
<i>I REALLY DON'T</i>
<i>SEE THE POINT.</i>

179
00:14:33,573 --> 00:14:36,274
EVERY MAN FOR HIMSELF
IN MY OPINION.

180
00:14:37,576 --> 00:14:39,878
THAT'S A LONELY WAY
OF THINKING, SON.

181
00:14:40,579 --> 00:14:42,513
YOUR CHOICE.

182
00:14:42,515 --> 00:14:43,648
I CARE ABOUT THIS TOWN.

183
00:14:45,651 --> 00:14:47,185
THE GOOD LORD HAS
BURDENED MY HEART

184
00:14:47,187 --> 00:14:48,920
AND I SEE IT AS MY DUTY
TO PROTECT 'EM.

185
00:14:56,195 --> 00:14:58,897
Woman:
<i>SUSIE WENT OUT</i>
<i>NIGHT BEFORE LAST</i>

186
00:14:58,899 --> 00:15:00,164
AND SHE HASN'T COME HOME.

187
00:15:02,268 --> 00:15:03,968
Sheriff:
<i>WAS SHE ALONE?</i>

188
00:15:04,937 --> 00:15:07,305
THERE WAS A PARTY
OR SOMETHING.  I...

189
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:10,275
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE THEY WENT.

190
00:15:12,912 --> 00:15:14,646
( whispers )
I TOLD HER WE COULDN'T
AFFORD IT.

191
00:15:16,282 --> 00:15:17,582
HEY.

192
00:15:17,584 --> 00:15:19,918
IT'S OKAY, MARGO.

193
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:21,552
GO AHEAD.

194
00:15:21,554 --> 00:15:23,922
SHE WANTS TO GO
TO THE UNIVERSITY.

195
00:15:23,924 --> 00:15:25,924
I TOLD HER
WE COULDN'T AFFORD IT,
SHE STORMED OUT

196
00:15:25,926 --> 00:15:27,592
AND THAT'S THE LAST TIME
I SAW HER.

197
00:15:27,594 --> 00:15:30,495
I'VE BEEN WORKING
AT WAYNE FLEENER'S,
THE GRAVEYARD SHIFT,

198
00:15:30,497 --> 00:15:32,964
AND I'VE BEEN
SAVING EVERY PENNY
THAT I CAN AND I--

199
00:15:32,966 --> 00:15:34,599
IT'S JUST--

200
00:15:36,468 --> 00:15:38,603
DO YOU MIND
IF I KEEP THIS?

201
00:15:39,939 --> 00:15:41,706
CAN YOU TELL ME
IF SHE HAS A BOYFRIEND,

202
00:15:41,708 --> 00:15:44,108
- A BEST FRIEND?
- UH, YEAH.

203
00:15:44,110 --> 00:15:46,945
THERE'S THIS KID
NATHAN MILLER.

204
00:15:46,947 --> 00:15:48,713
- SHE KNOWS I DON'T APPROVE.
- AND WHY IS THAT?

205
00:15:48,715 --> 00:15:50,648
'CAUSE HE'S GOT
ONE THING ON HIS MIND

206
00:15:50,650 --> 00:15:53,685
AND SUSIE'S NOT VERY GOOD
AT TELLING HIM NO.

207
00:15:54,987 --> 00:15:57,255
SHE'S DEAD, ISN'T SHE?

208
00:15:57,257 --> 00:15:59,157
NO.  NO NO NO NO.

209
00:15:59,159 --> 00:16:01,960
LET'S DON'T JUMP
TO CONCLUSIONS, OKAY?

210
00:16:01,962 --> 00:16:03,728
I'M SURE SHE'S FINE.

211
00:16:11,637 --> 00:16:14,505
I USED TO SPEAK
WITH SOMEONE
IN SAN FRANCISCO,

212
00:16:14,507 --> 00:16:16,341
BUT I'M FINE.

213
00:16:17,609 --> 00:16:20,345
MY HUSBAND, HE INSISTED
I COME SEE YOU.

214
00:16:24,717 --> 00:16:28,486
OUR DAUGHTER WAS
KILLED IN AN ACCIDENT
A FEW MONTHS AGO.

215
00:16:28,488 --> 00:16:31,022
WHAT HAPPEN TO HER?

216
00:16:43,736 --> 00:16:46,104
( loud splash )

217
00:16:46,106 --> 00:16:48,639
( rushing water )

218
00:16:48,641 --> 00:16:50,041
( gasps )

219
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:03,721
<i>YOUR DAUGHTER HAS BEEN</i>
<i>A HUGE PART OF YOUR LIFE.</i>

220
00:17:05,057 --> 00:17:07,625
IF YOU WEREN'T THROWN
OFF-GUARD BY THIS,

221
00:17:07,627 --> 00:17:09,727
THEN SOMETHING
WOULD BE WRONG.

222
00:17:09,729 --> 00:17:12,330
MY HUSBAND BLAMES ME
FOR HER DEATH.

223
00:17:12,332 --> 00:17:14,399
HAVE YOU FORGIVEN YOURSELF?

224
00:17:16,035 --> 00:17:18,136
THINGS HAVEN'T BEEN
THE SAME SINCE.

225
00:17:18,138 --> 00:17:19,704
HE WON'T TALK TO ME.

226
00:17:19,706 --> 00:17:21,506
HE WON'T TOUCH ME.  HE--

227
